obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39907)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the State of Nagaland Act, 1962.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39907&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39908)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39908&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the day which the Central Government may, by notifiation in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) "article" means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "assembly constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have the same meanings as in the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(d) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument or custom or usage having the force of law;`
  line
  line `(e) "Naga Hills-Tuensang Area" means the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area specified in Part B of the`
  line `Table appended to paragraph 20 of the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution, comprising the areas which`
  line `at the commencement of the Constitution were known as the Naga-Hills District and the Naga Tribal`
  line Area;
  line
  line `(f) "regional council" means the regional council referred to in article 371A.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39909)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of State of Nagaland.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39909&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, there shall be formed a new`
  line `State to be known as the State of Nagaland comprising the territories which immediately before that day`
  line `were comprised in the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area and thereupon the said territories shall cease to form`
  line `part of the State of Assam.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the power of the State Government to alter after the appointed day, the name,`
  line `extent or boundaries of any district, the State of Nagaland shall consist of three districts to be called the`
  line `Kohima district, Mokokchung district and Tuensang district, each comprising the areas respectively set`
  line `out in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39910)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39910&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES"—`
  line
  line `(a) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Assam, the following shall be added`
  line `at the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `"and the territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the State of Nagaland`
  line `Act, 1962";`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 15, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"16. Nagaland . . . . . The territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the State of`
  line `Nagaland Act, 1962".`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39911)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of Sixth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39911&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the Sixth`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution—`
  line
  line `(a) in paragraph 20—`
  line
  line `(i) sub-paragraph (2B) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-paragraph (3), the brackets and words "(other than the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area)"`
  line `shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) in the Table appended to paragraph 20, in Part B, the item "2. The Naga Hills-Tuensang Area"`
  line `shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39912)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Representation in Council of States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39912&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be allotted one seat to the State of Nagaland in the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(b) in the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table—`
  line
  line `(i) entries 16 to 19 shall be renumbered as entries 17 to 20;`
  line
  line `(ii) after entry 15, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"16. Nagaland. . . . . . . . . . . . . . .1",`
  line
  line `(iii) at the end, for the figures "224", the figures "225" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39913)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Election to fill vacancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39913&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the appointed day, there shall be held an`
  line `election to fill the seat allotted to the State of Nagaland in the Council of States.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39914)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39914&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The term of office of the member for the first time elected to fill the seat allotted`
  line `to the State of Nagaland in the Council of States shall expire on the 2nd day of April, 1968.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39915)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Representation in House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39915&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be allotted one seat to the State of Nagaland in the House of the People;`
  line
  line `(b) in the First Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950),—`
  line
  line `(i) the entry "25. Naga Hills-Tuensang Area. . . . . . . . .1" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) entries 16 to 24 shall be renumbered as entries 17 to 25;`
  line
  line `(iii) after entry 15, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"16. Nagaland. . . . . . . . . . . . . . .1".`
  line
  line `(2) The whole of the State of Nagaland shall form one parliamentary consituency to be called the`
  line `parliamentary constituency of Nagaland for the purpose of filling the seat allotted to that State in the`
  line `House of the People.`
  line
  line `(3) For the period referred to in clause (2) of article 371A, section 13D of the Representation of the`
  line `People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), shall apply in relation to the parliamentary constituency of Nagaland with`
  line `the modification that it shall be necessary to prepare and revise separately the electoral roll for that part of`
  line `the said parliamentary constituency which comprises the Tuensang district and the provisions of Part III`
  line `of that Act shall apply in relation to the said part as they apply in relation to an assembly constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39916)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Provision as to sitting member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39916&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The sitting member of the House of the People representing,`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area shall, as from that day, represent`
  line `the State of Nagaland in that House and shall continue to do so until a person is elected in accordance`
  line `with law to fill the seat allotted to the parliamentary constituency of Nagaland.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39917)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Strength of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39917&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The total number of seats to be filled by persons chosen`
  line `by direct election in the Legislative Assembly of Nagaland shall be 60:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the period referred to in clause (2) of article 371A, the total number of seats in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Nagaiand shall be ^1`
  line `[52], of which—`
  line
  line `(a)`
  line ^2
  line `[twelve seats] shall be allocated to the Tuensang district and shall be filled by persons chosen`
  line `by the members of the regional council from amongst themselves in such manner as the Governor,`
  line `after consulting that council, may by notification in the Official Gazette specify, and`
  line
  line `(b) the remaining forty seats shall be filled by persons chosen by direct election from assembly`
  line `constituencies in the rest of the State of Nagaland.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950),—`
  line
  line `(a) in section 7, the following proviso shall be inserted at the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `"Provided that for the period referred to in clause (2) of article 371A, the total number of`
  line `seats allotted to the Legislative Assembly of Nagaland shall be 46, of which—`
  line
  line `(a) six seats shall be allocated to the Tuensang district and shall be filled by persons`
  line `chosen by the members of the regional council referred to in that article from amongst`
  line `themselves in such manner as the Governor, after consulting that council, may by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette specify, and`
  line
  line `(b) the remaining forty seats shall be filled by persons chosen by direct election from`
  line `assembly constituencies in the rest of the State of Nagaland.;`
  line
  line `(b) in the Second Schedule, after entry 14, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `15. Nagaland..... [60 for the period referred to in clause (2) of articles 371A, 46].".`
  line
  line `(3) In the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951), in section 5, in clause (c), the`
  line `following proviso shall be inserted at the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `"Provided that for the period referred to in clause (2) of article 371A, a person shall not be`
  line `qualified to be chosen to fill any seat allocated to the Tuensang district in the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Nagaland unless he is a member of the regional council referred to in that article.".`
  line
  line `(4) The Election Commission shall delimit the assembly constituencies in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Constitution on the basis of the latest census figures, and in doing so the Commission`
  line `shall have regard to the following provisions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, consist of geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication, public convenience and linguistic affinities of the people,`
  line
  line `(b) all constituencies shall be single-member constituencies, and`
  line
  line `(c) the population of each constituency shall not, as far as practicable, be more than six thousand.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purpose of assisting the Election Commission in the performance of its functions under`
  line `this section, the Commission shall associate with itself five persons of whom three shall be elected by the`
  line `members of the Interim Body established under section 3 of the Nagaland (Transitional Provisions)`
  line `Regulation, 1961 (Regulation 2 of 1961), from among themselves and two shall be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the said associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of`
  line `the Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(6) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) formulate its proposals in regard to the matters mentioned in sub-section (4) and publish them`
  line `in the Official Gazette of the State of Assam and in such other manner as the Commission may`
  line `consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections and suggestions in relation to the proposals and`
  line `specifying a date on or after which the proposals will be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line `specified, and for the purpose of such consideration hold one or more public sittings at such place or`
  line `places as it may think fit;`
  line
  line `(c) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified, determine the matters mentioned in sub-section (4) by one or more final orders and`
  line `cause such order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette of the State of Assam; and upon`
  line `such publication the order or orders shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in question`
  line `in any court;`
  line
  line `(d) amend the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1961, so as to`
  line `include therein the parliamentary constituency of Nagaland and the assembly constituencies delimited`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 61 of 1968, s. 3, for "46" (w.e.f. 31-12-1968).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "six seats" (w.e.f. 31-12-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39918)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39918&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The rules as to procedure and conduct of business in force immediately`
  line `before the appointed day with respect to the Legislative Assembly of Assam shall, until rules are made`
  line `under clause (1) of article 208, have effect in relation to the Legislative Assembly of Nagaland, subject to`
  line `such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Speaker thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39919)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Common High Court for Assam and Nagaland.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39919&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be a common High Court for the State of Assam and the State of Nagaland to be`
  line `called the High Court of Assam and Nagaland (hereinafter referred to as the common High Court);`
  line
  line `(b) the Judges of the High Court of Assam holding office immediately before that day shall,`
  line `unless they have elected otherwise, become on that day the Judges of the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Expenditure in respect of the salaries and allowances of the Judges of the common High Court`
  line `shall be allocated between the State of Assam and the State of Nagaland in such proportion as the`
  line `President may by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39920)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provision as to Advocates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39920&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in section 3, in sub-section (1), for clause (b), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(b) for the States of Assam and Nagaland and the Union Territory of Manipur, to be known`
  line `as the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland;";`
  line
  line `(b) the Bar Council of Assam shall be deemed to be the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the`
  line `High Court of Assam shall be entitled to practise as an advocate in the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) All persons who immediately before the appointed day are advocates on the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of Assam shall as from that day become advocates on the roll of the Bar Council of Assam and`
  line Nagaland.
  line
  line `(4) The right of audience in the common High Court shall be regulated in accordance with the like`
  line `principles as, immediately before the appointed day, are in force with respect to the right of audience in`
  line `the High Court of Assam:`
  line
  line `Provided that as between the Advocate-General of Assam and the Advocate-General of Nagaland the`
  line `right of audience shall be determined with reference to their respective dates of enrolment as advocates.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39921)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Practice and procedure in common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39921&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the`
  line `law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High`
  line `Court of Assam shall, with necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39922)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Custody of Seal of common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39922&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day with respect to the custody of the Seal of the High Court of Assam shall, with necessary`
  line `modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the Seal of the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39923)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39923&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Assam`
  line `shall, with necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other processes used,`
  line `issued or awarded by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39924)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39924&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Assam and with`
  line `respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with necessary modifications, apply`
  line `in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39925)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Principal seat of common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39925&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The principal seat of the common High Court shall,`
  line `unless otherwise determined by the Chief Justice after consultation with the Governors of Assam and`
  line `Nagaland, be at the same place as the principal seat of the High Court of Assam immediately before the`
  line `appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39926)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39926&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Assam and the Judges and`
  line `division courts thereof shall, with necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39927)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Pending suits, appeals and proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39927&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `All suits, appeals and proceedings, civil, criminal or`
  line `otherwise, pending in the High Court of Assam immediately before the appointed day shall, on that day,`
  line `stand removed to the common High Court and the common High Court shall have jurisdiction to hear and`
  line `determine the same, and the judgments, decrees, sentences and orders of the High Court of Assam`
  line `delivered, passed or made before the appointed day shall have the same force and effect as if they had`
  line `been delivered, passed or made by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39928)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39928&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The President may, at any`
  line `time before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State of`
  line `Nagaland as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the appointed`
  line `day, pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of the State of Nagaland:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Nagaland may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Nagaland for any period`
  line `not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (39929)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 23
  title `Allowances and privileges of Governor of Nagaland.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 35 of 1981, s. 2 (w.e.f. 26-7-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39929&sectionno=22A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[22A. Allowances and privileges of Governor of Nagaland.—The allowances and privileges of the`
  line `Governor of Nagaland shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under clause (3)`
  line `of article 158, be such as the President may, by order, determine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39930)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39930&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The President shall by order determine the grants-in-aid of the`
  line `revenues of the State of Nagaland and the share of that State in the Union duties of excise, estate duty and`
  line `taxes on income and for that purpose amend thereby the relevant provisions of the Union Duties of Excise`
  line `(Distribution) Act, 1962 (3 of 1962), the Additional Duties of Excise (Goods of Special Importance)`
  line `Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), the Estate Duty (Distribution) Act, 1962 (9 of 1962), and the Constitution`
  line `(Distribution of Revenues) Order, 1962 (C.O. 63), in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39931)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Property, assets, rights, liabilities and obligations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39931&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) All property and assets situated in, or`
  line `used for, or in connection with the administration of, the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area and vested in the`
  line `Union immediately before the appointed day (other than any property or assets so vested for purposes of`
  line `the Union) shall, as from that day, vest in the State of Nagaland:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cash balances in the treasuries in the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area immediately before`
  line `the appointed day shall, as from that day, vest in the State of Nagaland.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligations of the Central Government, whether arising out of any`
  line `contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before the appointed day, the rights, liabilities and`
  line `obligations of the Central Government arising out of or in connection with the administration of the Naga`
  line `Hills-Tuensang Area shall, as from that day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Government of`
  line `the State of Nagaland.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39932)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39932&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover arrears of any tax or duty (being a tax or duty`
  line `enumerated in the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution) which have fallen due in the`
  line `Naga Hills-Tuensang Area shall pass to the State of Nagaland.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39933)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Continuance of existing laws and their adaptation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39933&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, in the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area shall continue to be in force in the State of Nagaland`
  line `until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of Nagaland of any law made`
  line `before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, within two years from that day, by order`
  line `make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be`
  line `necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and`
  line `modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other competent`
  line authority.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means, as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, the Central`
  line `Government; and as respects any other law, the Government of Nagaland.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39934)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39934&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 26 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in`
  line `relation to the State of Nagaland, construe the law in such manner not affecting the substance as may be`
  line `necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39935)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Provisions as to continuance of courts and of officers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39935&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) All courts and tribunals and all`
  line `authorities discharging lawful functions throughout the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area or any part thereof`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall, unless their continuance is inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act or until other provision is made by a competent Legislature or other competent authority,`
  line `continue to exercise their respective functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who, immediately before the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of`
  line `any post or office in connection with the administration of the Naga Hills-Tuensang Area or any part`
  line `thereof shall, except where by virtue or in consequence of the provisions of this Act such post or office`
  line `ceases to exist on that day, continue to hold the same post or office in the State of Nagaland, and shall be`
  line `deemed, as from that day, to have been duly appointed to such post or office by the Government of, or`
  line `other appropriate authority in, such State.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority, after the appointed`
  line `day, from passing in relation to any such person any order affecting his continuance in such post or office.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39936)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39936&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in section 15 of the States`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1956, in clause (c), for the words, "and Assam", the words "Assam and Nagaland"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39937)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Effect of provisions of Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39937&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39938)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39938&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39939)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 35 of 1981, s. 3, for "in which it is so laid" (w.e.f. 26-7-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39939&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session ^1`
  line [immediately
  line `following the session] or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39940)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413&sectionId=39940&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00025_196227_1517807321413
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `[Regulation 2 of 1961.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1974 (56 of 1978), s. 2 and the`
  line `First Schedule (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
